Surgical management of Pott's paraplegia. A series of 19 patients suffering Pott's paraplegia was reviewed in a ten-year period. Ever since their admission they were submitted to an antiphthisic and orthopedic medical treatment for 3 to four weeks. A medullar decompression by reaching the focus through different surgical technics was performed on 16 of them. 3 did not require such procedure 14 recovered completely